Program: Outlook
Title: 28/06/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00hffc8
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 29 Jun 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world: today, the other Tahrir Square - an Iraqi woman activist describes an attack on peaceful protesters in Baghdad. Also, how rickshaw pullers and plantation workers in Bangladesh paid for their own village school. And Larry Joe, the South African criminal turned pop star. Show less